<br>
I'm a rogue in his 21th season on Karana server and i'll have to duel a necro lvl 22 in the arena for a guild event. I've raised my poison skills so i can use contact, injected, blind, root and snare poisons yet.<br>
<br>
And now the questions :<br>
<br>
- Are there special tricks to duel necros for a rogue ?<br>
<br>
- Which poison may provide the more help ? i think snare or blind poison are the best but i don't have experience of PvP on Norrath (my only experience is PvP in hardcore mode in Diablo 2 (lots of salt when you know that if you die you loose you char))<br>
<br>
- I have a Bloodstained Fang (9/32) as primary and a Stiletto of the Bloodclaw (6/23) as secondary. I'll may have a Tombcarver (5/17) soon. Which one is better as primary weapon ? (knowing that i'll surely have 40+ ench and shaman buffs (50% haste, rune iii, resists, SoW, etc...))<br>
<br>
- What is the exact effect of the pumice stone ? all (de)buffs away ? one (de)buff ? 4 (de)buffs ?<br>
<br>
Hehe first duel with a necro, i think it'll be fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-------<br>
Malky aka Binouzours <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/18/01 11:20:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.armstrongsupply.com/images/bigtwink.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> If the fight is limited in area, such as the arena, you will be better off than if it is unlimited and the necro can shadowstep wherever they want.<br>
<br>
Use a muscle lock poison if unlimited area.  Blind if in the arena.<br>
<br>
Fast attacks to disrupt spell casting.  Stick to the necro and manuever for BS when it cycles.<br>
<br>
Pumice to get rid of DoT's.<br>
<br>
On blue servers I think you can still fear the pet.  If your Instill Doubt is maxxed, you may want to try this.  The pet will hammer you and stun you frequently.  If you fail on first attempt, stick to the necro.<br>
<br>
Necros are tough because of Pets, DoT's, and a nearly unresistable spell line that hurts you at the same time it heals them.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/18/01 1:06:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/Kambic/TRINITY.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> Fear the pet, be careful dont let him fear kite you :)<br>
<br>
Get as much MR/PR/DR gear as you can. Dunno what's up with those big buffs you are getting, but get some resist ones if you're getting buffed up.<br>
<br>
Pumice is -2 buffs/debuffs.<br>
<br>
 <p><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/bscreamspvp"><img src="http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/sig/joyous.gif"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceescritdabossalini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceescrit da Bossalini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/18/01 2:08:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> Ignore the pet.  Am I wrong or don't we get fear until level 22?  Even so, you won't be able to fear the pet easily, even with maxed skill for your level I wouldn't think.<br>
<br>
If your MR isn't up in the 80s, you might be SOL if they manage to get some distance and land a darkness on you.  You won't be able to pumice yourself with a pet beating on you either.<br>
<br>
My best advice at your level, charge the necro with a root/snare poison and just hack away, taking great care to land those backstabs (MAX YOUR SKILLS PvP ROGUES!).  Then pray that your poison don't wear off too fast.<br>
<br>
If all else fails, and you get darkened, and can't fear the pet to pumice yourself, bring a good bow and hope to interrept those spells with your arrows (MAX ARCHERY SKILL!!!) untill darkness wears off and you can catch him.<br>
<br>
Use straffe-run and jump to catch up to him faster and land some blows before he gets the next spell off.<br>
<br>
Most important thing to have when dueling a necro, MAGIC RESISTS.  With 90-100+ MR and a good set of weapons, necro's were never nothing more than fodder to me.  Pet or no pet, poison or no poison.  If anything, they would just always shadowstep/gate away.<br>
<br>
Oh, and it sucks worse because you're on a blue server, and they can fear you too.  MR is your friend... <p><font size=4 face=Times New Roman, serif><b>Ceescrit Bossalini</font><BR>
Retired Roag of VZ<BR>
<a href=http://www.eqrogue.com>Order of the Black Rose</b></a> <BR>
--------------------------------<BR><i>
"Where is the end to all my misery, is there a close?  I suppose that's why I murder my foes..."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/18/01 3:04:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/Kambic/TRINITY.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> Oh yeah I forgot about the ID level :/<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umalwae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>malwae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/18/01 3:07:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/atsila/pictures/Malsig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> Splurge on some really expensive range weapons.  If you do archery, pay out the nose for some long range hard hitting arrows.  If you do throwing, pay a smith to make you forged javelins, which have pretty good range and damage.  You will probably spend much of the fight rooted, unless you have crazy magic resist.  Going up against a necro, I'd sacrifce armor class for magic resistance.  One good slot for that is the bracers; you can get 7+ magic resist bracers, which helps a lot.  (Wolf's eye/gold, I think?).  Also, if you have the choice, go for the fastest weapons you can; sacrifice damage if necessary.  Necros don't have a lot of hit points.  Interrupting their spells will be more important than doing high amounts of damage per hit. <p><img src=http://members.home.net/atsila/pictures/Malsig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/18/01 3:13:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> Cheap MR gear:<br>
7mr bracers from a jewler<br>
bloodstained mantle<br>
dwarven ringmail tunic/sanark emblazoned talbred<br>
blackened alloy/iron crown<br>
9mr necklace from a jewler(200pp or so)<br>
Ravenscale gloves<br>
mask of deception<br>
<br>
thats basicly what i'm wearing... it adds around 55mr.  It's enough to make root/snare/darkness either not land at all, or break a few seconds after they land. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uugliitchybottom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugli Itchybottom</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/18/01 3:31:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> Necros don't get root until 34.  Just stay on em and hope you resist darkness. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/18/01 6:00:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> First of all, why all the uber buffs?  The only true way to fight/duel this necro is for you both to use what you have.  Nothing more.  Adding all those buffs, especially if you both have the same buffs, does NOTHING for the combat.  Don't allow buffs from others in this duel.<br>
<br>
Ok, on to the fight.  Most of the advice here is right on so I don't need to add much.  <br>
<br>
Ignore that pet.  You won't be able to ID it anyway, so paying attention to it will only seal your doom.  Now when I played on Bertoxxulous, pets wouldn't aggro on you in duels unless you attacked them OR if the caster made the pet after the duel started.  If that's still the case, then don't attack the pet and it won't attack you (even when you attack it's master).  They may have changed this, but that's the way it used to be...I'd do some research/testing.<br>
<br>
If the pet can attack you, you *may* want to consider hitting IT with root/snare/blind instead of the necro so it can't stay on your butt and stun you.  Stuns are very annoying.<br>
<br>
Regarding the necro, equip lots of MR stuff.  If you can keep darkness off you you'll have a chance.  If darkness holds you're in trouble.<br>
<br>
Keep on his butt (I'd use that tombcarver if in fact you can get it) to keep hitting him for interupts.  The damage won't be fantastic, but he will have a hell of a time casting.  Look for open backstab chances (save that backstab until you can use it).<br>
<br>
For poisoning him:  Blind in an arena.  Snare or root in the open.  <br>
<br>
Morvran McGuinness, Shanks  VZ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/18/01 7:57:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> arrows do not interrupt spells, but thrown weapons do. <p>Diabalein Avidya <br>
 Practicing Proctologist for 35 Lvls Of Pure Anal Probing Fun<br>173 Points of Loving, Hand Delivered on the End of a Sharp Stick</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufreonsmurf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FreonSmurf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/18/01 11:43:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> Remember necros line of spells are poison/disease based, and they might have some buffs up, so make sure ya have a backup plan if your poison is resisted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceescritdabossalini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceescrit da Bossalini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/19/01 9:06:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> &quot;arrows do not interrupt spells, but thrown weapons do. &quot;<br>
